isCorrectDatabaseImplementation

public boolean isCorrectDatabaseImplementation(java.sql.Connection conn)
                                        throws JDBCException
Drops all objects owned by the connected user. The Sybase functionality overrides this and does not remove the Foreign Keys. Unfortunately it appears to be a problem with the Drivers, see the JTDS driver page. http://sourceforge.net/tracker/index.php?func=detail&aid=1471425&group_id=33291&atid=407762
